SenSen Networks Limited – Q4 FY25 Quarterly Report Summary

Key Financial Highlights (AUD)

  • First full-year positive operating cash flow: $1.9M vs. prior comparative period (PCP) loss of ($1.3M).
  • Record annual cash collections: $14.1M (up 13% YoY).

  • Net cash position: $0.7M (vs. PCP net debt of $0.7M).
  • Closing cash balance: $2.83M (vs. $2.42M last quarter).
  • Undrawn debt facility: $1.15M.

Material Business Updates

  • Montréal project delivered: $1.5M revenue recognized (cash expected Q1 FY26).

Capital Structure & Liquidity

  • Total borrowings: $2.15M (down from $2.27M YoY).
  • No equity/debt raising announced.

Forward-Looking Catalyst

  • Montréal payment collection (~$1.5M) expected next quarter.

Summary of ASX Announcement (New Age Exploration Limited - Quarterly Activities Report, June 2025)

Key Operational Highlights

  1. Wagyu Gold Project (Pilbara, WA)
  2. High-grade gold intercepts from maiden RC drill program:
    • 8m @ 5.0g/t Au (including 1m @ 28.6g/t Au)
    • 4m @ 2.5g/t Au, 12m @ 1.0g/t Au, 3m @ 2.8g/t Au
  3. 1km of continuous mineralisation confirmed across Target 1 and Target 10.
  4. Supergene gold zones remain open along strike/depth; analogous to Hemi Gold Project (11.2Moz).

  5. Next phase: Expand oxide zones and test deeper primary mineralisation.

  6. Lammerlaw Project (New Zealand)

  7. Phase 1 drilling completed (5 holes, 458m); assays pending.
  8. Permit EP 61110 secured, expanding Otago footprint.
  9. Phase 2 drilling planned for Q1 2026.

Financial & Corporate Updates

  • Cash Balance (30 June 2025): A$557k (down from A$1.96m prior quarter).
  • Lochinvar Coal Project Sale: Completed post-quarter, granting NAE a A$1/tonne royalty (first 15Mt).
  • Funding Runway: 0.42 quarters of operating cash (per Appendix 5B); reliant on future capital raises.

Material Risks

  • Limited cash reserves (A$557k) with significant exploration commitments.
  • High-grade results at Wagyu suggest potential, but resource delineation pending.

Verdict: Exploration success at Wagyu is material, but liquidity concerns may pressure near-term valuation.

  • EPS Impact:
  • FY2024: $0.33 diluted EPS (pro forma).
  • 9M 2025: $0.34 diluted EPS (pro forma).

Operational Adjustments

  • Divestitures: Berry’s Specialty Tapes and HHNF businesses excluded (discontinued ops).
  • Cost Synergies: Not quantified; excludes integration benefits.

Key Risks

  • Preliminary Allocation: Fair value estimates for assets/liabilities subject to finalization.
  • Tax Assumptions: Blended 21% rate used; may change post-close.

Next Steps

  • SEC Filing: Pro forma financials attached (Form 8-K/A) for detailed adjustments.
